title: For Sale/Trade:  CAUTION to sellers in the Jacksonville area. PLEASE READ.
postcontent:
Ealier this week I posted a firearm for sale and recieved a few offers. A few nights ago someone texted me expressing interest but was unable to meet due to his work schedule, until late at night. I was not able to meet him for a days as well due to my wifes work schedule and activities with our children. 

I went to meet him in a public place tonight (12/03) but when the time approached he explained that he was unable to leave his house because his wife had left for work. I dumbly agreed to meet him at his house which was located off of Foy Lockamy Rd in Jacksonville. I called him for directions because my gps didn't take me exactly to a home. I was told there was a black Ford Taurus in the driveway, and stayed on the phone with him while pulling in the driveway. 

I told him I was there, and then was told "Step out of your truck if you want to see your wife and kids again." I put my vehicle in reverse immediately, narrowly avoiding being stuck in a ditch.

PLEASE. If you agree to meet someone, make sure it is in a public place, and be cautious of anyone texting from REDACTED off of Foy Lockamy Road.

The barrel and receiver are in perfect condition as well. Comes with a sling and a Tasco 6x24x40 scope that's in great condition as well. The 25-06 is a necked down version of the 30-06 and its known for its VERY FLAT trajectory which makes it a great deer cartridge all the way down to varmints. A very high velocity round with a lot of range.
